https://youtu.be/l-FDFsHA20wYwRulz2SneWHPhKk</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/ewcM8N7</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[DrunkKingOfImgur]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Extremely bittersweet.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/4YBn3La</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/jRL7hxI.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/oKPWCyP.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>This was an absolute dream costume for me. I had been a member of the 501st Legion and Mandalorian Mercs for a few years when I got the opportunity to purchase the entire thing from someone relatively local who was my size and build. I got to wear it onsttage for a John Williams symphony event, at conventions, for pet adoption...

Then a medical issue left me disabled. I haven't been physically capable of wearing the suit since 2021, with little hope of improvement. I haven't been able to work, I'm still waiting on a disability ruling, and now we have to move...possibly twice. I need the space, I need the money.

The same day I put it up for sale to my local Star Wars groups, it sold. I got my asking price for the entire thing (barely below what I paid). They came and picked it up. It's staying local. I could not have asked for a quicker, smoother, easier sale into better circumstances. It will see use again instead of gathering dust.

